      "writtenOn": "2026-06-10T10:20:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m reluctant to reuse the very old issue 943 here, because:\n* it\u0027s very out of date. for example, it doesn\u0027t define `allows` nor `isValid`\n* it\u0027s too generic. it also includes other builtins like `must` or `range`\n* it already has unrelated discussion in it. so any proposal feedback would feel out of place\n\nSo I think we should create a new mini-proposal for these reflect builtins, reflecting the spec design that\u0027s in this stack. It may seem a little silly, but that way people can comment on it.\n\nAnd then I would close 943 in favor of this new proposal plus separate issues for any other builtins that we still think may be useful. For example, \"must\" already has its own separate issue in https://github.com/cue-lang/cue/issues/575.",
      "revId": "e0ed88320ecc20b993078e267b0d205c09b20019",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
