      "writtenOn": "2026-06-10T10:20:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "why are we declaring a new Experiment type? we haven\u0027t done this in the past, so this feels inconsistent and unnecessary.",
      "revId": "e0ed88320ecc20b993078e267b0d205c09b20019",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e3b97bcc_738821d4",
        "filename": "internal/cueexperiment/file.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 116,
      "author": {
        "id": 1013536
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-06-10T13:21:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The typed *Experiment bundles two things a data-driven, compile-time gate needs: the enablement check (the closure) and the name used in the \"requires @experiment(%s)\" error. The existing Pos().Experiment().X pattern (structcmp, shortcircuit, ...) works for hand-written eval-time checks, but a gated builtin is data — adt.Builtin carries the gate as a field and verifyVersion rejects the reference at compile time, which is better UX than failing during evaluation.\n\nThat said, I\u0027m happy to collapse it to a plain func(*File) bool field plus a name string on the Builtin if you\u0027d prefer to avoid the named type. Leaving open for your call.",
      "parentUuid": "12d7a124_9c1287a1",
      "revId": "e0ed88320ecc20b993078e267b0d205c09b20019",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e0415323_48bf3d7f",
        "filename": "internal/cueexperiment/file.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 127,
      "author": {
        "id": 1017720
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-06-10T10:20:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think the name \"reflect\" may be a bit too generic. For example, if we want to add a language feature or builtins later on to inspect a value\u0027s optional and required fields, or to otherwise do any sort of type/schema reflection, then it would be difficult to add an experiment for it as we already had a \"reflect\" experiment.\n\nhow about any of these, to more clearly say \"the builtins that replace comparisons to bottom\":\n* `compbottom`\n* `bottombuiltins`\n* `reflectbuiltins` (though this one is not as precise)",
      "revId": "e0ed88320ecc20b993078e267b0d205c09b20019",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
